$aarPowDefensive = [
	"body armor (artificial)" => "<p>XcharnameX possesses artificially-created armor that provides protection and possibly a way of possessing other Powers. Armor comes in many forms of exotic plate-mail, nuclear-powered exoskeletons, or mechanically-created force fields.</p>

	<p>NOTE: The player should work with the members of staff to create armor which properly represents your character, and fits the look and feel of the site. The player can also determine which Powers are possessed by XcharnameX and which are properties of the armor. Any powers built into the armor can later be modified and enhanced; think of the changes Tony Stark has made iover the years to the Iron Man armor. On the other hand, powers that are built into the armor may possibly suffer from mechanical failure. The Armor' Power rank determines its durability and ability to resist/reduce damage.</p>",


	"force field" => "<p>XcharnameX possesses the ability to generate a protective barrier around XgenderXself which is proof against a wide variety of forces, including brute force, energy attacks and extreme temperature conditions. It can be projected and or used for a variety of feats.</p>

	<p>The force field completely absorbs any and all damage which might be caused by attack which is equal to or less in Intensity than that of their fields Power Rank. If The Intensity of the attack is higher than that of the field, then the attack is reduced by the fields power rank. The remaining Intensity breaches the field and affects anyone within by This diminished effect.</p>",


	"reflection" => "<p>XcharnameX can turn any attack sent against Xhim-her-themX back onto the attacker. The attack may be of any nature: brute force, Power, or even magic. The Power absorbs the energy of the attack equal to or less then it' intensity rank and redirects it back at  XcharnameX would attacker. If the attack' Intensity is higher than that of XcharnameX' reflection power rank, some of the damage will passes through and affect  XcharnameX.  XcharnameX can use Reflection indefinitely, so long as it isn&#039;t overcome by superior force. After The first time  XcharnameX' reflection is breached, it becomes inactive for one hour for each rank of intensitity the assaulting for was then that of the reflection</p>",


	"resistance (emotion attacks)" => "<p>XcharnameX has increased resistance to emotion-based attacks. Such attacks include Emotion Control, Hallucinations, Domination, and attacks aimed at their Intuition.  XcharnameX can ignore attacks with Intensities less than that of their power rank/willpower (depending on which is greater), and may reduce damage from higher level attacks by  XcharnameX' resistance.</p>",


	"resistance (energy attacks)" => "<p>XcharnameX has an increased resistance to any energy broadcast against them, whether artificial, natural, or Power-based. Such attacks include Light, Heat, Flame, Plasma, Hard radiation, Electricity, Vibration, Sonics, Cold, and Kinetic Bolts (most of the Energy Emission category).  XcharnameX can ignore attacks with Intensities less than  XcharnameX Power rank and may reduce higher level attacks by  XcharnameX own Power Rank.</p>",


	"resistance (magic attacks)" => "<p>XcharnameX has increased resistance to magic based attacks.  XcharnameX can ignore attacks with Intensities less than  XcharnameX Power rank and may reduce higher level attacks by  XcharnameX own Power Rank.</p>",


	"resistance (mental attacks)" => "<p>XcharnameX has increased resistance to psychic assualts and attacks aimed at  XcharnameX mind and/or neural system. Such attacks include psionics, neural manipulation, and any other attacks aimed at the mind or they&#039;re willpower.  XcharnameX can ignore attacks with Intensities less than  XcharnameX Power rank and may reduce higher level attacks by  XcharnameX own Power Rank.</p>",


	"resistance (physical attack)" => "<p>XcharnameX has an increased resistance to any physical attack (blunt or kinetic). This includes brute force, chemical weapons, biochemicals, disease, hostile environments, and temperature extremes. The XcharnameX can ignore any physical attacks with Intensities less than that of the Power rank, and may reduce damage from higher level attacks by XcharnameX own Power Rank.  XcharnameX can ignore attacks with Intensities less than XcharnameX Power rank and may reduce higher level attacks by  XcharnameX' own Power Rank.</p>",


	"resistance (power manipulation)" => "<p>XcharnameX has increased resistance to attacks that directly affect XcharnameX Powers. Such attacks include Weakness Creation, Power Control, Power Domination, Magic Control, and Magical Domination.</p>

	<p>XcharnameX can ignore any attack whose rank is less than that of  XcharnameX power rank. XcharnameX may reduce the effectiveness of higher level attacks by XcharnameX own Power Rank.</p>",


	"resistance (Vampirism)" => "<p>XcharnameX has increased resistance to any vampiric-type attacks. Such attacks include forms of Psi, Bio, Energy, Magic, and Power Vampirism.  XcharnameX can ignore any vampiric attack whose rank is less than this Power' rank. XcharnameX can reduce The effectiveness of the vampire' attack by deducting  XcharnameX Power Rank from the vampiric attack' Power rank.  XcharnameX can ignore attacks with Intensities less than  XcharnameX own Power rank and may reduce higher level attacks by  XcharnameX own Power Rank.</p>"
];



$aarPowDetection = [
	"360&deg; perception" => "<p>XcharnameX is aware of his local environment, allowing  XcharnameX to perceive their entire local surrounds as if  XcharnameX had a three -</strong>dimensional map in their head. Because of this,  XcharnameX is not reliance on  XcharnameX eyes for perceiving their surroundings. Thus, it is enarly impossible to blindside or to sneak up on  XcharnameX. as they have in effect a 360 degree field of &#34;vision&#34;.  XcharnameX is immune to the effects of invisibility and darkness unless such effects directly effect the mind.</p>",


	"abnormal sensitivity" => "<p>XcharnameX' senses function in their normal manner but their normal range of sensitivity is altered. The senses detect what they normally cannot and cannot detect what they normally can.</p>

	<p>This affects either vision or hearing. the former case,  XcharnameX sees infrared and ultraviolet light, radio waves, and radiation. In the latter case,  XcharnameX hears e  XcharnameX tremely high and low pitches.</p>

	<p>This may be considered a handicap human characters while for aliens this could be a fact of life. A XcharnameX can turn it into an advantage by devising a mean.of negating the senses of his adversary that doesn&#039;t hinder his own altered senses.</p>",


	"circular vision (360)" => "<p>XcharnameX can see 360 degrees around  XcharnameX.</p>",


	"danger sense" => "<p>XcharnameX can sense moments before a dangerous situation is about to occur, and usually from what direction such danger will emminate. Simply put, sense danger notifies  XcharnameX when they are about to be endangered. It is a limited form of Precognition. This power is often given different names, and like most mental powers, varies greatly from person to person. Spider -</strong>Man' danger sense is called his 'pider -</strong>sense&#039;, and alerts him when danger is near, though he does not always know the specifics of the danger. Additionally, this sense may warn when others are lying to them if such lies would endanger the  XcharnameX.</p>",


	"detection (biological life)" => "<p>XcharnameX can detect and identify biological, genetic and/or related phenomena.  XcharnameX can detect and discern the differences between both comple  XcharnameX and simple life forms. As such, they can sense the difference between human and an anemba, a cat and a dog or a human and a mutant.  XcharnameX can identify the those they&#039;ve met before; identify the specific persons with an Amazing rank; and on an Unearthly FEAT, provided  XcharnameX knows of the user,  XcharnameX can identify the actual possessor of the psionic power.</p>",


	"detection (energy)" => "<p>XcharnameX can detect and identify energy and related phenomena.  XcharnameX can only detect actual energy, not potential energy (it couldn&#039;t detect a bomb until it e  XcharnameX plodes, for example). Likewise, while it can detect the energies consciously emitted by superhumans, it cannot detect the super humans themselves.</p>",


	"detection (extra dimensional)" => "<p>XcharnameX can sense across dimensional barriers and see things existing in other dimensions. These include Asgard, the Astral Plane, Avalon, the Dark Dimension, the Demon Dimension, etc. The power rank number equals the number of different dimensions into which  XcharnameX can see.</p>",


	"detection (magic)" => "<p>XcharnameX can detect and identify magic and its effects.  XcharnameX can detect both magic in actual use and in potential. As such, this is another way to detect mutants, although it cannot differentiate them from normal magic-users.  XcharnameX can identify the past use of magic, identifys the caster if familiar to them, and in some instances identify the actual spell.</p>",


	"detection (power)" => "<p>XcharnameX can detect and identify superhuman Powers and can function as &#34;Mutant Detection.&#34; XcharnameX can also identify specific superhumans by their characteristic Powers (an Unearthly FEAT).  XcharnameX can identify the presence of previously invoked power when e  XcharnameX amining former targets of Power of a Good Intensity or greater within there sphere of detection.</p>",


	"detection (psionic)" => "<p>XcharnameX can detect and identify psionic Power and related phenomena. It can detect both actual psionics and the potential to use them. As such, this is the last way to detect mutants.  XcharnameX can identify the past use of psionics on a living subject on an E  XcharnameX cellent Intensity FEAT; identify the specific psionic Power on an Amazing Intensity FEAT; and on an Unearthly FEAT, provided  XcharnameX knows of the user,  XcharnameX can identify the actual possessor of the psionic power.</p>",


	"detection (weakness)" => "<p>XcharnameX can detect flaws and stress points in a target. This doesn&#039;t guarantee  XcharnameX can exploit this knowledge, though. The rank determines the types of weaknesses  XcharnameX can sense.</p>",


	"dimensional vision" => "<p>XcharnameX can sense across the dimensional barrier and see things existing in other dimensions and/or vibratory planes</p>",


	"Elemental Sense" => "<p>XcharnameX can immediately identify the elemental compostion and structure of an object and determine structural weaknesses (if any) on contact with the object. This is a subconscious, intuitive.</p>",


	"hyper-hearing" => "<p>XcharnameX can detect e  XcharnameX tremely faint sounds and unusual frequencies.  XcharnameX can identify objects by the sounds they emit. Because of the sensitivity of  XcharnameX hearing,  XcharnameX is more vulnerable to sonic attacks (which receive a +1RS against  XcharnameX.</p>",


	"hyper-olfactory" => "<p>XcharnameX can detect the presence of minute traces of substances and accurately identify them by smell. This Power is continually functioning</p>",


	"hyper-taste" => "<p>XcharnameX can detect the presence of minute traces of substances and accurately identify them by taste. This Power is continually functioning;  XcharnameX has learned to ignore unpleasant smells. If he loses  XcharnameX ability to mask out nasty odors, he&#039;ll be so distracted (and possibly sickened) by the intruding odors that he loses 1 endurance rank per day the condition persists</p>",


	"hyper-touch" => "<p>XcharnameX possesses an Enhanced sense of touch that permits  XcharnameX to detect e  XcharnameX tremely fine surface details and to identify materials by their surface &#34;feel.&#34;</p>",


	"microscopic vision" => "<p>XcharnameX' eyes can focus on e  XcharnameX tremely minute targets, objects too small for normal vision to perceive. This Power functions in two stages. The first is light magnification;  XcharnameX' eyes function as normal microscopes. This allows  XcharnameX to see things as small as chromosomes. Beyond this level, light no longer carries information. The second stage of this Power is a variation of Clairvoyance that permits  XcharnameX to see miniature, rather than distant, targets</p>",


	"radar sense" => "<p>XcharnameX can gain a three -</strong>dimensional picture of his surroundings through the use of electromagnetic waves.  XcharnameX both emits and senses these waves.  XcharnameX can use the Power to locate and identify targets by their characteristic echoes.</p>
		<br>
	Because of  XcharnameX' sensitivity to electromagnetic waves,  XcharnameX has an increased vulnerability to electrical and magnetic attacks; these may temporarily negate Radarsense.</p>",


	"shadow sight" => "<p>Unlike most people who walk the Earth,  XcharnameX is at home in the shadows. As such  XcharnameX is not hindered by the absence of light as others might be and can see perfectly well regardless of how dark it is, natural or otherwise.</p>",


	"sonar" => "<p>XcharnameX can gain a three-dimensional picture of his environment through the use of soundwaves. The Power allows  XcharnameX to locate and identify targets by the way they reflect sound.
</p><p>
	There are two ways this Power can operate. Passive Sonar utilizes existing sound. Active Sonar uses special sounds emitted by  XcharnameX (this is how bats and dolphins do it). The latter form requires a special adaptation of  XcharnameX' voice; otherwise there is no real difference between them. Because of the special sensitivity of  XcharnameX' hearing,  XcharnameX is vulnerable to sonic attacks.</p>",


	"temporal sensitivity" => "<p>XcharnameX' physical senses function in such a way as to be able to &#039;perceive&#039; actions and events regardless of the rate, speed, or temporal factor in which such events might unfold. Likewise  XcharnameX physical senses can now sense/detect when extra-ordinary temporal events are occurring. This sensitivity may allow  XcharnameX a limited amount of post/precognitive abilities.</p>",


	"telescopic vision" => "<p>XcharnameX' eyes can focus on e  XcharnameX tremely distant targets, objects too far away for the unaided eye to perceive.  XcharnameX eyes function as normal binoculars. This allows  XcharnameX to see things regardless of distant so long as they aren&#039;t obstructed by the curvature of the planet, light pollution, etc.</p>",


	"thermal vision" => "<p>XcharnameX can see infrared light and heat images. This allows  XcharnameX to see in the dark, perceive temperature differences (especially those left by a living person' contact with an object), and partially see through solids. In the last case,  XcharnameX can only see the heat patterns of objects touching the other side of the barrier.  XcharnameX can judge the temperature of a target by its thermal color.  XcharnameX has an increased risk of being blinded by strong heat sources, even those that don&#039;t affect normal vision (-1R). Thermal vision may be a consciously-activated mode or the XcharnameX' normal means of vision.</p>",


	"tracking" => "<p>XcharnameX can detect and follow the tracks left by a specific target.  XcharnameX can detect environmental and spatial disturbances with the result that at high ranks  XcharnameX can actually track across deep space.</p>",


	"True Sight" => "<p>XcharnameX can see the correct image of a target, despite any attempts at concealment or disguise it. This Power can penetrate any means of hiding something' true nature, whether physical, psionic, illusionary, or power-based. True Sight can penetrate any disguise at or below its rank. Range is limited to one area unless the Power is coupled with a Power that e  XcharnameX tends his vision (Telescopic Vision, for example). The Power may be automatic or deliberate.</p>",


	"ultraviolet vision" => "<p>XcharnameX can see ultraviolet light. Because UV light isn&#039;t as readily absorbed by water as normal light, this Power enables  XcharnameX to see clearly through fog and at greater distance in the water (+1rs).  XcharnameX can also see the dim light given off by radioactive materials.  XcharnameX cannot actually &#34;see in the dark&#34;but only if UV light is present. The effect is the same when seen by normal people.  XcharnameX has an increased risk of being blinded by strong UV sources, like black lights and radiation.</p>",


	"x-ray vision" => "<p>This is commonly called &#34;x-ray vision&#34; but is not actually based on the emission of x-rays.  XcharnameX can see through any solid with the exception of lead; the effect is as if the obscuring material were transformed to clear glass. If this Power is interfered with by outside forces,  XcharnameX may perceives everything as a transparent outline."
];



$aarPowEnergyControl = [
	"catalytic control" => "<p>XcharnameX can control the speed at which chemical reactions occur. XcharnameX can increase or decrease the energies emitted or drained in such reactions by XcharnameX Power rank number. For example, XcharnameX could increase the heat, emitted by exothermic reactions like oxidation; XcharnameX could also increase the chilling effect of endothermic reactions. XcharnameX can increase or decrease the speed or rate at which reactions occur, like stopping iron from dissolving in acid or causing steel to rapidly transform into rust. XcharnameX can also develop a variety of Power stunts:</p>
